<div class="your-rights">
    <div class="chevron-div"><img class="chevron" src="chevron-double-right.png"></div>
    <div class="question-div"><b><p class="title">If agents ask to enter your home.<br>Ask the following questions:</p></b></div>

      <div class="rights-container">
        <ul>
            <li><p>"Do you have a warrant?".</p></li>

            <li><p>If they don’t have a warrant, you do not have to let them into your home.</p></li>

            <li><p>Please slide the warrant under the door.</p></li>

            <li><p>A valid warrant must be signed by an Immigration Court Judge. A warrant issued by DHS or ICE without a Judge’s signature is invalid. Look for a signature from a Judge at the top of the document.</p></li>

            <li><p>You do not need to open your door to the officers unless they show you a valid search or arrest warrant naming you or a person living at your address.</p></li>

            <li><p>If there is no valid reason for their entry, declare: "I do not consent to your entry."</p></li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <br>
    <br>
